# Beachwalk Villas — Environment Variables

## Cloudflare Web Analytics (optional)
# Set this to enable Cloudflare Web Analytics on your site.
# Get your beacon token from Cloudflare dashboard → Web Analytics → Add site
# If unset, the analytics beacon will not load (clean local/dev builds)
PUBLIC_CF_BEACON_TOKEN=your_beacon_token_here

## Contact form (Web3Forms)
# The contact/inquiry form submits to Web3Forms (works on a fully static site).
# Create a free access key at https://web3forms.com (enter the destination email),
# then paste it here. If unset, the form gracefully falls back to opening the
# visitor's email client (mailto:) so it still works in local/preview builds.
PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY=your_web3forms_access_key_here

## Note on Environment Variables with Cloudflare Adapter
# - Public variables (accessible in client/browser) must be prefixed with PUBLIC_
# - Private variables (server-only) can be used without prefix
# - In production, set these in Cloudflare Pages dashboard → Settings → Environment variables
